{
  "text": "whereu(t) is the vertical ground velocity, W is an appropriate time window containing the T phase, \u03c1 and \u03b1 are the density and the P-wave velocity of the shallow receiver structure, respectively. Following [CITATION_1] , we extend the time window W over the entire time axis, and then use Parseval's theorem to recast the computation of (1) into the frequency domain:",
